Class ListenerMessageThrottle

  • java.lang.Object

          • com.camerontec.catalys.server.processor.FIXListenerBase
            • com.camerontec.catalys.server.storeandforward.ListenerMessageThrottle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IComponent, IEndOfDayPerformer, IExceptionListener, IFIXListener, IFIXMessageProcessor, IHasAttributes, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IMessageListener, IMessageProcessor, IMessageSource, ICatalysEventListener, Cloneable, EventListener

    public class ListenerMessageThrottle
extends FIXListenerBase
    A kind of message buffer that restricts the number of messages that can pass through it in a given period. If more messages arrive in that period they are queued. This is for messages FROM the FIX session.

    The buffer is persisted so that it is not lost if the application restarts. This buffer can be configured by supplying the Listener Message Throttle with a nested Properties element containing Persisted Collection Properties.
